# RxJS Core Rules

- Use Observables for async streams and serial communication events.
- Use Promises only when they better represent one-shot async operations.
- Avoid nested subscriptions.
- Prefer RxJS operators over manual async orchestration when appropriate.
- Ensure subscriptions are cleaned up.
- Avoid leaking internal Subjects.
- Expose Observables rather than writable Subjects.
- Keep error handling explicit.
